This paper discusses the vulnerability of copyright detection systems to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks in copyright detection, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), computer vision (cs.CV), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
